WEBVTT

00:06.050 --> 00:08.733
Mark 10, 45.

00:09.594 --> 00:16.483
The Son of Man came not to be served.

00:18.526 --> 00:18.946
Stop.

00:19.066 --> 00:20.829
You don't need the rest of the verse to get the point.

00:22.050 --> 00:24.814
He came not to be served.

00:25.094 --> 00:30.601
Therefore, don't compromise the meaning of the incarnation by serving Christ.

00:31.763 --> 00:33.505
He came not to be served.

00:33.525 --> 00:34.546
Don't serve Him.

00:36.514 --> 00:42.463
It's easy to assume that the more I do for Jesus, the more faithful I am.

00:43.124 --> 00:44.486
But Piper flips that.

00:45.287 --> 00:46.048
I'm Dan Kruver.

00:46.669 --> 00:53.179
In this episode of Light and Truth, John Piper unpacks why Jesus came not to be served.

00:53.920 --> 00:57.645
And what that means for how we relate to him on a daily basis.

00:58.446 --> 01:06.418
This message was originally delivered in Wheaton, Illinois at the Act III Reformation Conference on October 29th, 1999.

01:10.434 --> 01:16.360
I'm going to begin with reflections upon the title and this term, the Excellency of God.

01:17.522 --> 01:20.204
I was reflecting on this word Excellency.

01:20.585 --> 01:27.192
This is by way of introduction to my particular topic about God being too excellent to need servants.

01:28.213 --> 01:33.859
So I want you to reflect with me for a moment on the term, the Excellency of God.

01:33.879 --> 01:36.562
And I want to do it by asking this particular question.

01:38.434 --> 01:54.395
Why do we in conferences like this or in certain churches or sermons put forward themes like this instead of just dealing with the simple gospel?

01:56.477 --> 01:59.101
Christ died for my sins according to the Scriptures.

01:59.822 --> 02:00.643
He was buried.

02:01.343 --> 02:06.450
He rose again triumphant over death and hell and Satan.

02:07.458 --> 02:21.671
Why don't you just deal with the simple, glorious facts of the gospel instead of these big, broad, overarching things like the excellency of God?

02:21.711 --> 02:23.133
What's the reason for that?

02:26.736 --> 02:27.677
Now there is a reason.

02:29.619 --> 02:37.266
It's very relevant to understanding the gospel and I would invite you to open your Bible by way of introduction to

02:38.594 --> 02:52.131
2 Corinthians chapter 4, I confess that I cannot distinguish in my mind very clearly between the term the excellency of God and the glory of God.

02:52.151 --> 02:55.876
And so I am taking them biblically as almost interchangeable.

02:59.180 --> 03:06.930
Read with me 2 Corinthians 4 verses 3 to 6.

03:08.002 --> 03:36.978
Even if our gospel is veiled, gospel, we're talking gospel here now, even if our gospel is veiled, it is veiled to those who are perishing, in whose case the God of this world has blinded the minds of the unbelieving so that they might not see, now these next words are some of the most important words in my estimation in all the Bible, in understanding the nature of conversion and the nature of the gospel.

03:38.402 --> 03:47.811
And they recur again in verse six, but let's read them carefully and attend to every phrase that they might not see the gospel.

03:47.871 --> 03:54.658
Now define it for us, Paul, tell us what you mean of the glory of Christ.

03:55.539 --> 03:56.620
That's the gospel.

04:00.443 --> 04:07.410
The gospel is the gospel, the excellency of Christ.

04:08.226 --> 04:16.418
is the gospel, or at least is an essential component of the gospel.

04:16.438 --> 04:16.998
You see that?

04:17.018 --> 04:22.026
I'm not adding any words here, except replacing the word glory with Excellency.

04:23.087 --> 04:32.180
So that they might not see, this is the devil's aim, that they might not see the light of the gospel of the glory of Christ.

04:32.200 --> 04:36.466
The gospel is not preached where the glory of Christ is not exalted.

04:37.666 --> 04:42.692
And then it defines Christ, who is the image of God.

04:42.772 --> 04:48.960
So the glory of Christ is the glory of God, which is now spoken again in verse six, but read five as well.

04:49.381 --> 05:00.435
For we do not preach ourselves, but Christ Jesus as Lord, a glorious Lord, an excellent Lord, and ourselves as your bond servants for Jesus' sake.

05:00.455 --> 05:06.002
For God who said light shall shine out of darkness is the one who has

05:06.082 --> 05:15.572
shown in our hearts to give, and now he repeats these words in slightly different arrangement.

05:15.592 --> 05:17.193
He's shown in our hearts to give what?

05:18.275 --> 05:21.478
The light that corresponds with light in verse 4.

05:21.578 --> 05:28.165
If you can read vertically here, you should let your eyes run up and down to link these words.

05:28.806 --> 05:32.449
Light in verse 4 with light in verse 6.

05:32.489 --> 05:33.170
You got that?

05:34.466 --> 05:47.150
of the knowledge, replacing of the gospel, of the glory of God instead of the glory of Christ, in the face of Christ instead of who is the image of God.

05:49.675 --> 05:55.506
That parallel is so rich, it would keep you for days, I believe, reflecting.

05:58.882 --> 06:01.385
But here's what I want you to see by way of introduction.

06:01.706 --> 06:16.744
As to why I love the theme of this conference, why the mission of our church is called, we exist to spread a passion for the supremacy of God in all things for the joy of all peoples.

06:17.545 --> 06:23.813
We've chosen the word supremacy, could have chosen glory, could have chosen excellency.

06:24.815 --> 06:27.538
The reason for words like this is because

06:27.618 --> 06:42.256
in order to be faithful to a text like this and to really penetrate to the essence and bottom of the gospel that must shine in the heart of person for them to be saved, there's got to be glory.

06:44.459 --> 06:50.446
Now let me just draw out a couple of implications of this to lead into my theme.

06:52.248 --> 06:54.711
The gospel is the gospel of the glory of Christ.

06:54.771 --> 06:56.914
That's not an implication, that's a quotation.

06:57.698 --> 07:01.845
The gospel is the gospel of the glory of Christ.

07:02.286 --> 07:06.212
The glory of Christ shines out of the gospel.

07:06.352 --> 07:08.295
It stands forth from the gospel.

07:08.536 --> 07:13.224
When you see the gospel for what it really is, you see glory.

07:13.244 --> 07:15.287
You see the glory of Christ.

07:15.547 --> 07:16.769
You see excellency.

07:20.195 --> 07:21.177
Here's an implication.

07:22.659 --> 07:24.402
To be saved

07:25.570 --> 07:30.737
One must experience 2 Corinthians 4-4 and 4-6.

07:32.339 --> 07:41.291
To be saved, one must experience 2 Corinthians 4-6 and 4-4.

07:44.976 --> 07:45.957
That's huge!

07:49.582 --> 07:55.410
Because it means that the gospel has to be preached in such a way as to

07:55.554 --> 08:10.152
lift up the gloriousness of it and the Holy Spirit has to work to illumine the heart by the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Christ.

08:10.633 --> 08:16.380
Shine in your heart because there's no life if it doesn't shine there and you're not saved.

08:18.683 --> 08:24.210
Now the reason I say the excellency of God is an important theme is because I love the gospel.

08:24.418 --> 08:27.001
You say, why don't you just preach the simple gospel?

08:27.302 --> 08:39.117
This is the essence of the gospel, the excellency of Jesus radiating out through his work of a perfectly lived life and atoning death.

08:40.259 --> 08:49.431
A triumphant resurrection is the revelation of the glory of Christ, who is God.

08:49.992 --> 08:51.634
And if you don't see it,

08:51.938 --> 08:55.542
as glorious you are not born again.

08:55.602 --> 08:59.927
That's serious and that's the gospel.

09:01.028 --> 09:07.735
And there are a lot of non-born again professing Christians in the churches who have no taste for the glory of God.

09:09.117 --> 09:09.917
And that's scary.

09:11.439 --> 09:16.084
No taste, no sight, taste and see, taste and see.

09:17.706 --> 09:21.650
We're talking a spiritual seeing.

09:22.306 --> 09:26.511
Jesus said, seeing, they do not see and hearing, they do not hear.

09:26.752 --> 09:29.515
There are two seeing, folks, and there are two hearings.

09:30.657 --> 09:33.280
One is with this eyes and it saves nobody.

09:34.201 --> 09:39.228
One is with the eyes of the heart, as Paul called it, in Ephesians 1, 18, and it saves the soul.

09:41.050 --> 09:50.002
And you only can see with the eyes of the heart when verse 6 of 2 Corinthians 4 happens by grace.

09:50.082 --> 09:54.828
and you should plead with God to give it to you tonight if you don't have it.

09:57.612 --> 10:17.458
The glory of Christ in the gospel, in the cross, in the resurrection, in the perfect life of righteousness, in the ascension, in his reign and intercession for us in heaven, this story is glory.

10:18.338 --> 10:20.441
and you must taste it as glory.

10:21.262 --> 10:25.949
And that's the evidence you've been wrought upon by the living God to make you his own.

10:27.371 --> 10:29.855
No taste for glory, no salvation.

10:31.197 --> 10:32.499
And you don't make that happen.

10:32.999 --> 10:34.161
God makes that happen.

10:34.962 --> 10:43.955
The reason the gospel is so cheap today and there are so many nominal believers in our churches is because people ask the question I began with.

10:43.975 --> 10:45.938
Why don't you just preach the simple gospel?

10:46.210 --> 10:53.620
and lay aside these big, high, heavy, weighty theological themes like the excellency of God.

10:55.703 --> 11:13.667
Faith, the last implication before I move to the theme, faith is a seeing and savoring of the glory of God in the Gospel.

11:14.588 --> 11:15.730
That's the meaning

11:16.066 --> 11:17.728
of saving faith.

11:17.748 --> 11:27.439
A seeing and savoring of the glory of Christ who is the image of God.

11:28.500 --> 11:40.694
My whole enterprise of Christian hedonism is an effort to make plain the spiritual seeing and savoring.

11:40.774 --> 11:44.658
And all I mean by savoring is seeing it

11:44.994 --> 11:46.456
as precious.

11:48.779 --> 11:55.048
I reckon everything is lost for the surpassing value of knowing Christ Jesus, my Lord.

11:55.289 --> 12:01.698
Indeed, I count all things as rubbish that I might gain Christ.

12:01.999 --> 12:03.801
That's saving faith talking.

12:04.282 --> 12:06.926
That's not any add on to faith talking.

12:07.847 --> 12:12.754
Faith is a savoring, a treasuring

12:13.282 --> 12:19.108
a leaning on and loving and delighting in what you've seen in the gospel.

12:19.608 --> 12:37.805
That's why there's no difficulty moving from the glorious once for all work of justification in the moment of the first twinkling of an eye of saving faith to this process of sanctification because the faith that justifies is that kind of faith and it sanctifies.

12:38.806 --> 12:42.930
You can't not be holy when you love God like that.

12:45.314 --> 13:00.472
We have so gotten saving faith wrong by making it some kind of choice to believe a doctrine that people scratch their heads as to why they're not being changed.

13:01.874 --> 13:02.955
They're not born again.

13:03.736 --> 13:06.300
They've never seen glory as glory.

13:07.381 --> 13:08.702
Glory is precious.

13:09.083 --> 13:10.364
Glory is a treasure.

13:10.725 --> 13:13.769
Glory is that for which you count everything is lost.

13:13.809 --> 13:14.930
I've never seen it.

13:16.258 --> 13:19.382
Therefore, we're not on our faces as a church crying out.

13:19.842 --> 13:21.464
Oh, God, come with light.

13:22.385 --> 13:28.272
Do verse 6 of 2 Corinthians 4 in our churches because our people don't see it.

13:31.215 --> 13:34.699
You wonder why the early church died so easily?

13:35.079 --> 13:37.482
That is, the saints died so easily?

13:37.662 --> 13:42.648
How could they sing on the way to the stake or the lion?

13:43.729 --> 13:44.370
How could they do that?

13:45.730 --> 13:48.354
because to die is gain.

13:48.975 --> 13:57.349
My question now, how do you serve God so that His excellency is magnified and not compromised in your life?

13:58.731 --> 14:04.561
We have, this room is filled with servants of the Lord and I want to tell you to be a servant tonight.

14:06.624 --> 14:08.347
I'm basing it on X 17, 25.

14:10.170 --> 14:12.434
God is not served by human hands.

14:13.314 --> 14:17.740
as though he needed anything for he himself gives to all men life and breath and everything.

14:19.262 --> 14:22.246
Therefore, beware of serving God.

14:22.727 --> 14:25.811
Beware of serving God.

14:26.151 --> 14:29.416
You can dishonor God by serving God.

14:29.656 --> 14:31.118
That's what that text says.

14:31.138 --> 14:33.000
Let me give you another one just to add on to it.

14:34.422 --> 14:43.154
Mark 10, 45, the son of man came, not

14:43.810 --> 14:44.832
to be served.

14:46.815 --> 14:47.315
Stop.

14:47.335 --> 14:49.118
You don't need the rest of the verse to get the point.

14:52.003 --> 14:54.807
He came not to be served.

14:55.047 --> 15:00.576
Therefore, don't compromise the meaning of the incarnation by serving Christ.

15:02.900 --> 15:04.662
He came not to be served.

15:04.682 --> 15:05.584
Don't serve Him.

15:08.929 --> 15:10.171
So that needs to be heard.

15:10.852 --> 15:12.274
It needs to be wrestled with.

15:15.746 --> 15:17.828
Now this is a big issue to me.

15:18.609 --> 15:22.673
I wrote a whole book to try to explain what I mean called future grace.

15:24.094 --> 15:43.474
And what burdened me behind that book was an ethic out there of how to serve God that has a modicum of truth behind it that makes it almost the given way of articulating service to God today, which I think is not

15:44.834 --> 15:46.437
the most God-glorifying way.

15:46.677 --> 15:49.061
Namely, I've got different names for it.

15:49.181 --> 15:55.672
I sort of like the term the tanto ethic.

15:55.692 --> 16:09.013
But I realize I'm 53 and probably most young people in the room don't know the Lone Ranger and tanto and high-o silver and a white stallion and a black mask and a silver bullet.

16:09.113 --> 16:12.018
And that's just 50, sorry.

16:14.338 --> 16:25.371
But I like it because the Lone Ranger got into this relationship with Tonto, this Indian who helped him out of so many scrapes by saving his life.

16:26.713 --> 16:29.697
And it was the ethic of the Indian tribe that he saved the life.

16:29.797 --> 16:35.924
But once a man saves your life, then you bind yourself to him and you follow him and you serve him the rest of your life, saving his life.

16:36.004 --> 16:44.114
And so the whole story, year after year in the 50s, was Tonto rescuing poor Lone Ranger from all of his

16:44.354 --> 16:46.998
scrapes as he was trying to do good around the world.

16:48.901 --> 16:49.742
So you see where I'm hidden.

16:53.147 --> 17:00.318
God has saved you, and now your motivation is to serve him for the rest of your life and help him.

17:01.559 --> 17:06.887
Now nobody articulates their service of God that way, but I fear that it may come close.

17:08.069 --> 17:09.531
He gave, he gave his life for me.

17:09.591 --> 17:14.098
What have I given for him?

17:16.322 --> 17:19.085
Call it the debtor's ethic, that's probably the better term.

17:20.507 --> 17:27.314
God has done so much for me, and now out of gratitude, I will do and do and do for Him.

17:28.556 --> 17:35.503
So you look back to what He did for you, and as you turn to the future, what you see is a God whom you are to serve.

17:37.746 --> 17:45.234
There's something profoundly wrong with that, at least in its tendency, and the way it's lived out by many.

17:47.202 --> 17:57.416
Thank you for listening to this episode of Light and Truth, where we are committed to providing God-centered preaching to help you see Christ clearly and treasure Him truly.

17:57.997 --> 17:59.539
I'm your host, Dan Kruver.

18:00.440 --> 18:11.855
On our next episode, John Piper continues our eight-part series, Living and Dying for the Glory of Christ with a message titled, Down, Down, Down into Grace.

18:12.696 --> 18:13.497
I hope you'll join us.

18:14.279 --> 18:16.882
For more resources, visit Desiring God

18:17.058 --> 18:17.715
dot org.

